* Angus Hambro (1883–1957), British Conservative Party politician

The Conservative candidate was 54-year-old Captain Angus Hambro. He was Member of Parliament for South Dorset from 1910 to 1922. He became High Sheriff of Dorset in 1934.The New Sheriffs.The Times (London, England), Friday,  Mar 23, 1934; pg. 6; Issue 46710
The Amateur Champion Ernest Holderness was unavailable for work reasons. Angus Hambro was to have been captain and reserve but private affairs prevented him from travelling.
